# Spring Boot Core

Aligned with Spring Boot 4.0.x / Spring Framework 7.0.x.

## Application Structure
- Single `@SpringBootApplication` class at the root package
- Group by feature/domain, not by technical layer
- Package-private classes by default; only expose what is needed

## Annotations
- `@RestController` for REST endpoints (combines `@Controller` + `@ResponseBody`)
- `@Service` for business logic
- `@Repository` for data access (enables exception translation)
- Avoid `@Component` as a catch-all; use role-specific stereotypes

## Dependency Injection
- Constructor injection only (no `@Autowired` on fields or setters)
- Single constructor per bean (auto-detected by Spring)
- Mark dependencies `final`
- Use `@Qualifier` or `@Primary` for disambiguation

## Configuration
- `@ConfigurationProperties` with `@Validated` for type-safe config binding
- Fail-fast on invalid configuration at startup
- Externalize environment-specific values; never hardcode
- Use profiles (`@Profile`) for environment-specific beans

## Bean Lifecycle
- Default scope: singleton. Use `@Scope("prototype")` only when justified
- `@PostConstruct` for initialization; `@PreDestroy` for cleanup
- Graceful shutdown: configure `server.shutdown=graceful`

## Jakarta EE
- Use `jakarta.*` namespace exclusively
- Never mix `javax.annotation` / `javax.validation` with `jakarta.*`

## Virtual Threads
- Enable with `spring.threads.virtual.enabled=true` on supported stacks
- Appropriate for I/O-bound workloads; measure before enabling

